        "ResourceName": "Hinode SOT-SP Level 0 FITS",
        "ReleaseDate": "2026-05-26T00:08:46",
        "Description": "The Hinode Solar Optical Telescope Spectro-Polarimeter (SOT-SP) Level 0 FITS dataset consists of uncalibrated FITS files generated from spacecraft telemetry. The dataset contains spectro-polarimetric observations of the Fe I 630.15 nm and 630.25 nm spectral lines obtained with a slit spectrograph and polarization modulation system. The Level 0 FITS products preserve detector-oriented spectro-polarimetric measurements prior to scientific calibration and inversion processing. The observations include wavelength, slit spatial dimensions, polarization beam information, and Stokes measurements used for subsequent derivation of solar magnetic-field parameters.\n\nHinode is a Japanese mission developed and operated by JAXA in collaboration with NAOJ, NASA, STFC (UK), and international partners.",
        "PublicationInfo": {
          "Authors": "The Hinode SOT Consortium: National Astronomical Observatory of Japan (Japan); Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (Japan); Lockheed Martin Solar and Astrophysics Laboratory (USA)",
